    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  HbA1c level of 7.5% or less on stable dosages of sulphonylurea (glimepiride 1-6mg/day)
             and metformin (1-2g/day) for at least six weeks and BMI of 20-30 kg/m2.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  hepatic impairment, coronary artery disease and or heart failure, renal failure, those
             who requires insulin therapy or HbA1c &gt;7.5%, presence of macular edema and serum
             albumin &lt;3gm/dL.
      </textblock>
